MARK GETTY Mark Harris Getty , ( born July 9 , 1960 ) , is a British educated U.S. businessman who holds Irish citizenship and is co - founder of Getty Images .
A member of the Getty family , which originally made its money from oil , he is the son of American Gail Harris , and American - British billionaire philanthropist Sir John Paul Getty .
CAREER
Section::::Career .
Getty was born in Rome , Italy .
He attended Taunton School and studied Politics & Philosophy at St Catherine 's College , Oxford .
Getty began his career with spells at Kidder Peabody in New York and then joined Hambros Bank Limited in London .
He co - founded Getty Investments LLC Group , which is the majority shareholder of the photographic agency Getty Images , with Jonathan Klein in 1993 .
Getty is the chairman of Getty Images .
Under his leadership it has become a major supplier of both commercial and private photographs , especially for publications in the UK and US .
Getty is a member of the board of Getty Investments LLP .
In 2003 , Getty inherited his father 's majority holding in the Wisden Group .
In 2004 Getty was re - appointed as a trustee of the National Gallery in London .
In the Sunday Times Rich List 2018 ranking of the wealthiest people in the UK he was placed 383rd with an estimated family fortune of Â£ 325million .
PERSONAL LIFE Section::::Personal life .
In 1982 , Getty married Domitilla Harding , a member of the House of Lante Montefeltro della Rovere , at the Basilica of the Twelve Apostles in Rome .
Together they have three children .
His son Joseph married jewelry designer and socialite Sabine Ghanem at the same Basilica in May 2015 .
Getty and Harding divorced in 2011 .
In 2015 , Getty was awarded an honorary knighthood ( KBE ) for services to arts and philanthropy .
Getty is an Irish passport holder and lived at Wormsley Park in Buckinghamshire , England before returning to live in Rome , Italy , in 2017 .
